        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 5:58PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 558 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles north of Lake Valley, moving west at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
